WEBVTT

00:04.091 --> 00:06.049
- Previously
On "Good Girls"...

00:06.093 --> 00:07.224
- I had him
recall the nail polish.

00:07.268 --> 00:08.399
- What's that?

00:08.443 --> 00:09.618
- Oh, we had
to change the formula.

00:09.661 --> 00:11.141
- Change it back.

00:11.185 --> 00:13.317
- There is a nail salon
selling 'em for $200 a bottle.

00:13.361 --> 00:15.319
- Nail salon robbed.
Guess what they took.

00:15.363 --> 00:17.321
- I figured out
who we should help.

00:17.365 --> 00:18.453
I got their daughter's kidney.

00:18.496 --> 00:20.063
- You had pizza
with your therapist?

00:20.107 --> 00:21.673
- He's helping me.
It's like a study buddy.

00:21.717 --> 00:23.371
- I wanted to introduce you
to Lila.

00:23.414 --> 00:24.633
Thought you could use
a real tutor.

00:24.676 --> 00:27.114
- What are you guys into?
- We have fun.

00:27.157 --> 00:28.419
- Dr. Cohen.

00:28.463 --> 00:30.856
- I quit my job today.
- Why?

00:30.900 --> 00:32.597
- I kissed my boss.

00:32.641 --> 00:34.425
- We have enough
to hire Max's cousin.

00:34.469 --> 00:37.646
You're gonna need a sniper.
I know a guy.

00:37.689 --> 00:39.082
- How does this work?

00:39.126 --> 00:40.301
- Say I'm your lawyer--

00:40.344 --> 00:42.477
trial itself
will run you 60 grand.

00:42.520 --> 00:46.742
So how is Friday...
morning?

00:46.785 --> 00:48.700
- That works.

00:51.834 --> 00:53.923
- How are we
gonna know?

00:53.966 --> 00:57.448
- It's not like they're gonna
run his mugshots in the obits.

00:57.492 --> 00:59.885
- And do we get
a phone call or--

00:59.929 --> 01:04.629
- He just said 11:00 on Friday.

01:08.851 --> 01:10.548
- It's 10:56.

01:11.636 --> 01:14.857
- You're dead.
- No, you're dead.

01:14.900 --> 01:16.163
- You are!

01:19.818 --> 01:21.255
- 10:57.

01:24.171 --> 01:26.216
- It'll be good
to be normal again.

01:26.260 --> 01:29.480
- Be whatever we wanna be.
- Finally.

01:29.524 --> 01:31.003
- Dude.

01:31.047 --> 01:32.483
- I just wanna be
a good person again.

01:32.527 --> 01:36.270
- ♪ Why must it be?

01:36.313 --> 01:38.750
- Just some...

01:38.794 --> 01:41.492
normal mothers
with a lucrative side hustle...

01:41.536 --> 01:44.016
- ♪ They mean so much to me

01:44.060 --> 01:48.847
- Minus the...serial killing
extortionist psychopath.

01:50.153 --> 01:51.633
Know what I mean?

01:51.676 --> 01:52.938
- ♪ Do what you feel

01:54.636 --> 02:00.337
♪ Do what you feel is good
and do it right away ♪

02:00.381 --> 02:01.991
- The deed is done.

02:02.034 --> 02:04.385
- ♪ 'Cause it's for you,
my love ♪

02:04.428 --> 02:05.299
♪ And if you're ever around

02:05.342 --> 02:07.214
- How do you know?

02:07.257 --> 02:09.390
- Dog just looked at us.

02:12.001 --> 02:13.698
- So?

02:13.742 --> 02:17.746
- So...dogs don't just stop
and stare.

02:19.008 --> 02:21.141
His spirit has passed.

02:22.490 --> 02:24.666
- What time do you have?

02:27.756 --> 02:29.671
- 11:01.

02:29.714 --> 02:33.979
- ♪ To have you home,
have you home ♪

02:34.023 --> 02:36.156
- It's over.

02:37.505 --> 02:42.640
- ♪ To have you home

02:42.684 --> 02:45.208
- Darrel sees all the action
because he's a center.

02:45.252 --> 02:46.296
- Well, guess what.

02:46.340 --> 02:47.819
If you don't feed
Darrel the puck,

02:47.863 --> 02:49.256
he doesn't see anything.

02:49.299 --> 02:51.649
A great defensive man
keeps his team in the game.

02:51.693 --> 02:54.348
That's way more valuable
than scoring a couple points.

02:57.568 --> 02:59.657
Do you remember when...

02:59.701 --> 03:01.877
Darrel peed himself
in the third period?

03:03.922 --> 03:06.273
We all saw that.

03:06.316 --> 03:07.752
- We had to Zamboni.

03:09.537 --> 03:12.496
- Ah, ah, ah,
don't eat the fries.

03:15.760 --> 03:16.718
Okay.

03:23.333 --> 03:24.987
Here you go, my man.

03:25.030 --> 03:28.512
I threw in a little
extra hot sauce for you, so...

03:28.556 --> 03:30.688
- Where's the ranch?
- Oh, did you request that?

03:30.732 --> 03:33.300
- I put it in the notes area.
- Oh, I see the problem here.

03:33.343 --> 03:34.475
You put it
in the delivery notes,

03:34.518 --> 03:36.477
not the menu notes.

03:36.520 --> 03:37.869
- What's the difference?

03:37.913 --> 03:40.394
- Well, delivery note's more
for, like, a gate code

03:40.437 --> 03:41.656
or if the dog's out--

03:41.699 --> 03:43.571
- I can't eat wings
without ranch, dude.

03:43.614 --> 03:46.878
- Oh, yeah, sorry,
we don't do returns.

03:53.407 --> 03:55.235
Fries are yours.

03:59.935 --> 04:01.328
- Yo.

04:01.371 --> 04:02.503
- Yo, what's good, dog?

04:02.546 --> 04:03.939
- You remember
Uncle Darren, right?

04:03.982 --> 04:06.071
- Thought you were gonna be
with your tutor today.

04:06.115 --> 04:07.551
- I leveled up.
Tch.

04:07.595 --> 04:09.901
- I also offer college prep,
you know, when it's time.

04:09.945 --> 04:13.296
- Oh, he's gonna need
all the LSATs, GMATs, MCATs,

04:13.340 --> 04:14.819
all the ATs.

04:14.863 --> 04:17.692
- 'Cause I'm gonna be a lawyer,
doctor, Wall Streeter?

04:17.735 --> 04:19.607
- Okay, go do
your homework please.

04:19.650 --> 04:21.043
Go on.

04:21.086 --> 04:23.437
- Dream it, believe it, be it.

04:25.526 --> 04:27.571
Intense.
- Yeah.

04:27.615 --> 04:29.704
But, you know, he's
really counting on me,

04:29.747 --> 04:32.054
so I gotta pass this thing.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.925
- All right, so check it.

04:33.969 --> 04:37.320
300 for the ID, another hunny
for travel and incidentals.

04:37.364 --> 04:39.191
Then there's my fee--
that's another grand.

04:39.235 --> 04:41.672
- Well, how much to
just not look like a dummy?

04:41.716 --> 04:45.328
- Uh, same fee, but, you know,
for friends and family--

04:45.372 --> 04:47.591
yeah, I could finagle
a low-interest student loan.

04:47.635 --> 04:50.899
- You know what?
I'll just pay it.

04:59.386 --> 05:00.952
- Buh-buh-buh-bum!

05:07.002 --> 05:08.046
- Congratulations.

05:08.090 --> 05:09.613
- Couldn't have done it
without you.

05:13.356 --> 05:15.576
- Two, three, four.

05:15.619 --> 05:17.578
And exhale, two, three...

05:17.621 --> 05:19.841
- You sweat like cold cuts
on a counter.

05:20.972 --> 05:22.931
- Hey, put that back.
- I'm thirsty.

05:22.974 --> 05:25.803
- It's 10 bucks.
- You have to pay?

05:25.847 --> 05:27.718
- You don't?

05:27.762 --> 05:30.547
- DL Dave said
I could put stuff on his tab.

05:30.591 --> 05:33.681
- What?
- Two, three, four--

05:36.031 --> 05:38.338
Who can I plow
to get that arrangement?

05:38.381 --> 05:39.991
- Lisa from
counterterrorism's game.

05:40.035 --> 05:42.820
- Take it easy.
Now, what do we got?

05:44.909 --> 05:48.739
- Most of the women there
that day live in a shelter.

05:48.783 --> 05:52.177
- Mm, easy to pin it on.
- Or they just need the money.

05:52.221 --> 05:54.397
- Convenient.

05:54.441 --> 05:57.182
- That shade goes
for a lot on eBay.

05:57.226 --> 05:58.793
God knows why--it's dreadful.

06:01.361 --> 06:04.929
- Why were they there?
- Some weird church event.

06:04.973 --> 06:08.063
- Who planned it?
- You're fishing.

06:10.544 --> 06:11.849
- Figure out
who brought 'em in.

06:11.893 --> 06:14.374
- What are you gonna do?
- Raid your minibar.

06:14.417 --> 06:17.855
- I threw it all up already.
- You gotta stop doing that.

06:18.987 --> 06:21.076
- I need you to go
to the fancy grocery store.

06:24.732 --> 06:26.211
- My parents are coming?

06:26.255 --> 06:27.865
- It's way worse.
- Who?

06:29.563 --> 06:30.912
- Donor family.

06:32.783 --> 06:35.612
Sara invited them to dinner.

06:35.656 --> 06:37.832
- No.
- She's cleansing her soul.

06:37.875 --> 06:39.181
- What?

06:39.224 --> 06:41.575
Can't she, like,
save a rainforest or something?

06:41.618 --> 06:43.403
- I told her to do it.

06:45.666 --> 06:47.581
- We danced...
- I know.

06:47.624 --> 06:50.801
- The day their kid died.
- Baked potatoes, yeah?

06:50.845 --> 06:53.456
- Every holiday,
every birthday--

06:53.500 --> 06:55.632
- Twice baked--
everyone loves those.

06:55.676 --> 06:58.809
- Whenever I see my baby girl,
I wanna dance.

06:58.853 --> 07:00.550
- I know.

07:00.594 --> 07:02.639
- So how the hell am I supposed
to look those people in the eye

07:02.683 --> 07:04.641
when I danced
on their daughter's grave?

07:07.601 --> 07:08.950
- They're coming in
from Madison.

07:08.993 --> 07:10.734
- Call it off.

07:10.778 --> 07:13.824
- Our souls could use
some housekeeping too.

07:15.522 --> 07:17.741
I still need a dessert.

07:17.785 --> 07:19.308
- I'll make
my sweet potato pie.

07:23.965 --> 07:27.838
- ♪ Don't make me over

07:27.882 --> 07:34.497
♪ Now that I'd do
anything for you ♪

07:34.541 --> 07:38.109
♪ Don't make me over

07:38.153 --> 07:43.419
♪ Now that you know
how I adore you ♪

07:43.463 --> 07:47.771
♪ Don't pick
on the things I say ♪

07:47.815 --> 07:49.860
♪ The things I do

07:49.904 --> 07:54.386
♪ Just love me
with all my faults ♪

07:54.430 --> 07:56.954
♪ The way that I love you

07:56.998 --> 08:01.002
♪ I'm begging you

08:01.045 --> 08:04.484
♪ Don't make me over

08:04.527 --> 08:11.012
♪ Now that I can't make it
without you ♪

08:21.588 --> 08:24.112
- What are we celebrating?

08:33.817 --> 08:36.167
- Nothing.

08:40.563 --> 08:43.218
- I would just really like
to know where we're going.

08:43.261 --> 08:44.959
- Oh, you will.
- When?

08:45.002 --> 08:46.917
- When we get there.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.529
- If there's some kind
of problem--

08:49.572 --> 08:51.313
- How much cut have
you got now?

08:52.923 --> 08:54.534
- I don't know.

08:54.577 --> 08:56.579
- Where's it all going,
Elizabeth?

08:59.060 --> 09:01.149
- What do you mean?

09:01.192 --> 09:03.499
- What are you buying with it?

09:05.632 --> 09:07.895
Yeah, see?

09:07.938 --> 09:09.549
That's why we're here.

09:16.991 --> 09:19.080
Set me up, please.
Thank you.

09:41.015 --> 09:43.104
- Everything okay
with the last batch?

09:43.147 --> 09:44.453
- Mm-hmm.

09:47.935 --> 09:49.632
- We're actually
printing tonight,

09:49.676 --> 09:52.287
so if you, uh,
like if you wanted to,

09:52.330 --> 09:55.682
we could do the drop-off early.

09:55.725 --> 09:57.509
- That won't be necessary.

10:29.629 --> 10:33.110
- So last time you were cash
heavy, things got tricky...

10:33.154 --> 10:34.895
'cause you and your girls
went stupid

10:34.938 --> 10:36.723
and burned it with the Feds.

10:49.649 --> 10:53.000
You don't turn this properly,
you will attract attention.

10:53.043 --> 10:55.176
You need a system.

10:56.743 --> 10:59.267
I'ma ask you again.

10:59.310 --> 11:02.052
Where's it been goin'?

11:04.011 --> 11:05.708
- Somewhere safe.

11:05.752 --> 11:07.492
- What, like a mattress?

11:07.536 --> 11:10.321
- Yeah.
- Except you ain't got one.

11:12.715 --> 11:14.717
Where's the money going?

11:19.069 --> 11:20.941
- I can't tell you.

11:20.984 --> 11:23.595
- Then I can't cut you in
anymore.

11:29.776 --> 11:31.516
- You hungry?

11:31.560 --> 11:32.909
- No.

11:32.953 --> 11:34.955
- Mind if we stop at IHOP?

11:34.998 --> 11:37.218
- Who does he think
he is anyway, your father?

11:37.261 --> 11:39.655
I mean,
taking away your allowance?

11:39.699 --> 11:41.526
- How?!

11:41.570 --> 11:42.832
- It's like, what's next?
You know?

11:42.876 --> 11:45.052
Put away your toys
or you're grounded?

11:45.095 --> 11:47.141
- How is he still alive?

11:47.184 --> 11:49.230
- Hey, Dad, it's my money.
You know?

11:49.273 --> 11:50.405
It's like--

11:50.448 --> 11:52.624
- And, like, what am I
supposed to say?

11:52.668 --> 11:54.496
"Don't worry about it.
It went to a good cause.

11:54.539 --> 11:55.932
I put a hit out on you.

11:55.976 --> 11:58.413
- That did not happen.

11:58.456 --> 12:01.329
Unkillable.
Unhuman.

12:01.372 --> 12:03.070
- You know what
I would really love?

12:03.113 --> 12:05.594
Is if he would just show up at
one of your houses next time

12:05.637 --> 12:07.509
so you know what it's like
to think on your feet.

12:07.552 --> 12:11.208
- There shouldn't be a next
time 'cause we already paid.

12:11.252 --> 12:13.776
Old boy's gotta go.

12:15.473 --> 12:19.303
- Hi, I am here to see
a Mr. James Fitzpatrick.

12:21.218 --> 12:23.786
- Who, may I ask,
is inquiring?

12:23.830 --> 12:25.483
- Uh, a customer?

12:25.527 --> 12:28.704
- Yeah, a very upset customer,
so...

12:33.274 --> 12:35.798
- Uh, do you know
how much overnight costs?

12:37.844 --> 12:39.323
- I don't work here.

12:39.367 --> 12:41.456
- Oh, I'm sorry, I just--

12:41.499 --> 12:43.110
I thought
'cause of your shirt.

12:43.153 --> 12:45.852
- I can help you, sir.
- See...

12:47.244 --> 12:48.637
- I'm sorry,
but Mr. Fitzpatrick

12:48.680 --> 12:50.421
is not available at the moment.

12:50.465 --> 12:52.249
- But he's back there.

12:52.293 --> 12:54.425
- But not available.

12:54.469 --> 12:57.646
- Tell him that Beth is here.

12:57.689 --> 12:59.126
- Again, I am so sorry,
but I--

12:59.169 --> 13:01.781
- Boland.

13:01.824 --> 13:04.218
- Oh, hold on.

13:12.182 --> 13:14.489
He left something for you.

13:16.099 --> 13:18.493
- What the hell is this?

13:18.536 --> 13:20.321
- He said it was
like hiring a lawyer.

13:20.364 --> 13:21.844
They charge by the hour.

13:21.888 --> 13:24.804
- And then do nothing?
- Yes, like a lawyer.

13:27.807 --> 13:31.419
- 11,000 in incidentals.

13:31.462 --> 13:33.856
- I'm sorry,
why does he need the omakase

13:33.900 --> 13:35.162
to not kill gang friend?

13:35.205 --> 13:37.338
- And what is "OT"?

13:37.381 --> 13:40.689
- Occupational therapy
for manual dexterity.

13:40.732 --> 13:43.300
- What, like his trigger finger
is sore or something?

13:43.344 --> 13:45.041
How is that on us?

13:45.085 --> 13:46.347
- You guys...

13:48.131 --> 13:49.741
That's him.

13:49.785 --> 13:51.395
- That's him?

13:51.439 --> 13:54.094
Well, I'm telling his clown ass
that we're not paying

13:54.137 --> 13:56.531
for his spray tan sessions.

13:56.574 --> 13:58.925
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, hold up.

14:00.578 --> 14:02.972
- Oh, he plays the cello?
- That's a guitar.

14:03.016 --> 14:05.888
- It's a cello.
The case gives it away.

14:05.932 --> 14:07.107
Has a much narrower neck

14:07.150 --> 14:08.848
and a more
cambered fingerboard.

14:08.891 --> 14:10.458
- That's no cello.

14:25.516 --> 14:27.779
- Think he's gonna
smoke someone?

14:29.346 --> 14:30.957
- Oh, boy.

14:31.000 --> 14:33.568
- Here we go.

14:53.153 --> 14:56.199
- It's a mob hit.
Classic.

15:16.393 --> 15:17.960
- Nope.

15:18.004 --> 15:19.527
- Huh.

15:39.590 --> 15:41.984
- Oh, God.
Oh, my God!

15:42.028 --> 15:43.725
- Jesus.

15:43.768 --> 15:45.205
- Who would want her dead?

15:45.248 --> 15:46.946
- She looks so sweet!

15:55.867 --> 15:59.567
- I'd feel a whole lot better
if he carried a wallet.

16:22.546 --> 16:24.635
- Oh, my God, it's a school.

16:26.202 --> 16:28.161
- Oh, no.

16:29.858 --> 16:32.034
Oh, no, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no.

16:32.078 --> 16:33.775
- Daddy!

16:38.214 --> 16:40.564
- Hmm...

16:41.348 --> 16:43.089
- It's a cello.

16:51.488 --> 16:53.186
- Uh-oh.

16:56.363 --> 16:59.018
- We should get out of here.
- How?

17:00.802 --> 17:02.369
- He's already seen us.

17:02.412 --> 17:04.240
- And we've seen too much.

17:08.505 --> 17:10.072
- Do not.

17:13.162 --> 17:14.381
- What's he gonna do?

17:14.424 --> 17:16.078
- Give us a lollipop?

17:18.167 --> 17:20.082
- All right, fine, open it.

17:30.049 --> 17:32.094
- I didn't know
your daughter went here.

17:32.138 --> 17:35.358
It's got a great...
music program.

17:36.229 --> 17:39.188
- Ms. Marks, Ms. Hill.

17:39.232 --> 17:40.929
- Hey
- 'Sup?

17:40.972 --> 17:43.888
- Why are you following me?

17:43.932 --> 17:45.238
- Um...

17:47.022 --> 17:50.895
Just...curious...

17:50.939 --> 17:53.420
about the state of our lawsuit.

17:54.334 --> 17:55.987
- It's not moving forward.

17:56.031 --> 17:58.120
- We already paid for it.

17:58.164 --> 17:59.991
- Yeah,
and you billed us for more.

18:00.035 --> 18:03.125
- If you refer to article 3-A
in the contract you signed,

18:03.169 --> 18:05.475
I have the right to terminate
due to breach.

18:05.519 --> 18:07.303
- How did we breach?

18:07.347 --> 18:08.957
- Failure to disclose
the nature

18:09.000 --> 18:10.741
of your relationship
with the target.

18:10.785 --> 18:12.482
- What does that mean?

18:14.354 --> 18:17.096
- Which one of you engaged
in flagrante delicto?

18:17.139 --> 18:18.923
- Excuse me?

18:18.967 --> 18:20.447
- Who boned him?

18:22.797 --> 18:24.538
He go for a ride
on the jazzy?

18:26.017 --> 18:28.281
- What about you,
little bird?

18:28.324 --> 18:31.762
- Why does it matter?
- I don't do jilted lovers.

18:31.806 --> 18:34.765
- Uh, okay, no one was jilted.

18:34.809 --> 18:37.246
- There it is.

18:37.290 --> 18:39.683
- Come on, man.
It was one and done.

18:40.902 --> 18:43.078
- I mean,
for the most part.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.254
So this is where
you draw your line?

18:45.298 --> 18:47.082
- Crimes of passion
get messy.

18:47.126 --> 18:48.779
- Okay, again,
the word passion--

18:48.823 --> 18:51.086
- Clients, they have regrets,
they start talking.

18:51.130 --> 18:54.002
Before you know it, I have to
dispose of everyone involved.

18:55.177 --> 18:57.571
And on my own dime no less.

18:59.442 --> 19:02.010
- Well, we're not paying
for this.

19:02.793 --> 19:05.535
- You don't want this
going to collections.

19:10.584 --> 19:12.281
- Oh, my.

19:12.325 --> 19:14.718
- Is that his tongue?

19:18.026 --> 19:20.246
- It's a nasty process.

19:28.993 --> 19:30.821
- So here's your registration.

19:30.865 --> 19:32.127
Check the box for Muskegon.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.737
That's where my hookup is.
- Cool.

19:33.781 --> 19:37.132
Oh, hey, you know how you have
that friends and family loan?

19:37.176 --> 19:38.568
- How sick is this?
Look at this.

19:38.612 --> 19:41.049
Made the middle name Annie
so it's like, you know,

19:41.092 --> 19:42.920
named after my mom
or something.

19:42.964 --> 19:44.226
- That's tight.

19:44.270 --> 19:47.011
Um, instead of a loan...
- Same social though.

19:47.055 --> 19:49.362
- What about like a...
scholarship?

