- Bruh!

20:06.640 --> 20:09.338
- Dude, dude, dude, I had it.
- Dick move.

20:09.382 --> 20:10.513
- No, no, no, I just got hit

20:10.557 --> 20:13.081
with something
majorly big, okay?

20:13.124 --> 20:16.824
- You still owe me for the ID.

20:16.867 --> 20:18.521
- Come on, Boo.
It's just--

20:18.565 --> 20:21.220
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no,
no, no, I do this for you,

20:21.263 --> 20:23.570
every loser jonesing
for a diploma's

20:23.613 --> 20:25.833
gonna want a piece, so no.
Uh-uh.

20:25.876 --> 20:27.661
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

20:28.401 --> 20:30.229
How am I supposed to do this
without you?

20:30.272 --> 20:33.232
- I don't know.
Maybe study?

20:37.975 --> 20:39.542
- Thanks again
for making the trip.

20:39.586 --> 20:42.241
- Uh...I hope you
brought your appetite.

20:43.416 --> 20:46.027
- I hope this wasn't
too much trouble.

20:46.070 --> 20:47.811
- It was nothing.

20:47.855 --> 20:49.726
- Looks like Thanksgiving.

20:51.337 --> 20:53.730
- And we have so much
to be thankful for.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.821
- Well,
dig in, everyone.

20:57.865 --> 20:59.562
- Okay, let's, let's, uh...

20:59.606 --> 21:01.260
- See what happens, right?
- I'm so hungry.

21:03.871 --> 21:05.916
- Mmm.
Hmm?

21:05.960 --> 21:08.441
- I'm sorry.
Would you mind?

21:09.790 --> 21:11.400
- Ever since, uh...

21:13.010 --> 21:15.186
We always say a blessing.

21:17.319 --> 21:19.713
- Where did my manners go?
- Must be somewhere.

21:22.846 --> 21:25.284
- Okay.
Mmm.

21:30.419 --> 21:32.856
Okay.
Here we go.

21:32.900 --> 21:34.902
- Bless us, oh Lord,
for these thy gifts

21:34.945 --> 21:36.338
we are about to receive.

21:36.382 --> 21:39.080
Give us grateful hearts
for all thy mercies

21:39.123 --> 21:42.779
and bless our loved ones,
especially our dear Heather

21:42.823 --> 21:46.174
who we know would love
to be here tonight...

21:46.217 --> 21:48.045
but she is here, right hon?
- Mm-hmm.

21:48.089 --> 21:50.874
- And we thank you, Lord,
for carrying her spirit on

21:50.918 --> 21:52.615
in beautiful Sara.

21:55.139 --> 21:57.490
- Whew.
Wow.

22:00.231 --> 22:02.843
That ham though.

22:02.886 --> 22:05.106
Mm-hmm.
Thank you, Lord.

22:05.149 --> 22:06.455
- Oh.

22:06.499 --> 22:07.587
- Huh?

22:10.894 --> 22:11.852
- Stan.

22:17.292 --> 22:20.513
- Oh, okay, all right.

22:21.818 --> 22:22.776
Okay.

22:29.217 --> 22:31.828
- And Lord, you know...

22:33.569 --> 22:35.789
Um, everything Carl said...

22:37.225 --> 22:39.749
And, uh, just wanna

22:39.793 --> 22:41.751
thank you for blessing us
with the opportunity

22:41.795 --> 22:42.839
to meet these guys,

22:42.883 --> 22:45.494
and so happy and glad
my baby girl

22:45.538 --> 22:47.801
could make this happen.

22:47.844 --> 22:51.021
Obviously, you know,
we wished it was, uh,

22:51.065 --> 22:53.154
under different circumstances,
but, you know,

22:53.197 --> 22:57.201
you work in mysterious ways,
and God bless the food, amen.

22:57.245 --> 22:58.333
- Now can we eat?

22:58.377 --> 22:59.595
- Oh!

23:00.509 --> 23:03.947
- Yes.

23:03.991 --> 23:05.514
- Oh...
- So, um...

23:05.558 --> 23:07.429
how was the trip down?

23:07.473 --> 23:09.388
- Oh, we took the bus.

23:10.519 --> 23:13.217
- That's a...16-hour trip.

23:13.261 --> 23:15.002
- Oh, not for us.

23:15.045 --> 23:17.265
- We could only afford to go
as far as Kenosha,

23:17.308 --> 23:20.834
so we did
a bit of a ride share

23:20.877 --> 23:22.488
situation from there.

23:24.359 --> 23:26.405
- Where's your car?

23:26.448 --> 23:28.363
- Um...
- Oh.

23:28.407 --> 23:32.498
- We sold it
after, um, Carl lost his job.

23:35.457 --> 23:36.458
- But, you know,

23:36.502 --> 23:37.764
I've been doing
so much walking.

23:37.807 --> 23:40.419
I dropped my cholesterol
50 points.

23:40.462 --> 23:41.985
Doctor's pleased.

23:42.029 --> 23:43.813
So...

23:45.598 --> 23:46.903
- And the people at the church

23:46.947 --> 23:48.427
have been real kind,
pitching in.

23:48.470 --> 23:50.080
- Mm, yes.

23:50.124 --> 23:51.865
And what can you do?

23:51.908 --> 23:55.172
When life gives you lemons,
you can't rob a bank.

23:55.216 --> 23:57.044
- Ha ha ha ha!

24:01.440 --> 24:05.052
- So, um, how are you
gonna get back?

24:07.315 --> 24:09.796
- Can we buy 'em
a bus ticket?

24:10.666 --> 24:12.233
- Yeah.
- Oh.

24:12.276 --> 24:13.974
- We can work something out...
- We can work something out.

24:14.017 --> 24:17.499
- No, no, we're not here
for handouts.

24:17.543 --> 24:19.153
Although, I would try
some of those

24:19.196 --> 24:20.720
delicious-looking
mashed potatoes.

24:22.852 --> 24:24.506
- Here ya go.

24:25.507 --> 24:27.596
- No, from here it's easy.

24:27.640 --> 24:30.381
A daughter of a friend of ours
has offered to drive us

24:30.425 --> 24:31.861
as far as Lancing.

24:31.905 --> 24:34.777
And now, from there,
it's what many would call

24:34.821 --> 24:37.388
a scenic hike
up in God's country

24:37.432 --> 24:40.217
where, uh,
if my wife's ankles hold up,

24:40.261 --> 24:42.611
we'll just take one day
to get back to the interstate.

24:42.655 --> 24:44.874
- We'll work this off, huh?

24:44.918 --> 24:46.354
Good heavens!
- Well, we'll have to.

24:46.397 --> 24:50.140
- Such good people.
- I know.

24:50.184 --> 24:52.795
- We're not.
- I know.

24:58.279 --> 24:59.846
- How do we get back
to that?

25:17.690 --> 25:19.822
- Sweet potato pie
comin' in hot.

25:24.174 --> 25:26.699
- We still have
that pressure washer?

25:28.396 --> 25:29.832
- What is that?

25:29.876 --> 25:33.575
- Everyone wants hot sauce,
so I went to Costco.

25:33.619 --> 25:36.012
I got a vat of the stuff
and those little plastic cups

25:36.056 --> 25:38.580
so I could just dispense it
from the backseat.

25:38.624 --> 25:40.408
It's pretty smart, right?

25:40.451 --> 25:42.758
- It's why you're five star.

25:42.802 --> 25:47.067
- Yeah, well,
hot sauce in a hot car--

25:47.110 --> 25:48.677
- Oh, my God.
- Just...

25:48.721 --> 25:51.419
- Ugh!
- Everywhere.

25:56.424 --> 25:59.035
I'm so sorry, Beth.

25:59.079 --> 26:00.950
- Why?

26:04.650 --> 26:07.914
- 'Cause I--I can't do it.

26:10.481 --> 26:12.179
Then don't.

26:13.615 --> 26:15.312
Well, how are we
supposed to, I mean--

26:15.356 --> 26:18.446
+- Well, what do you wanna do?

26:21.101 --> 26:22.668
Hot tubs.

26:24.670 --> 26:28.021
Rich people love 'em,
negotiable prices--

26:30.458 --> 26:32.939
Financing plans, layaway--

26:32.982 --> 26:35.463
there's, like, a million ways
to cook the books.

26:37.944 --> 26:40.033
It's not regulated.
There's no licensing.

26:40.076 --> 26:42.426
Any idiot can sell them,

26:42.470 --> 26:44.603
and I know just the guy.

26:48.781 --> 26:51.435
You said I needed a system.

26:51.479 --> 26:53.133
This is my system.

26:53.176 --> 26:55.439
Sistema.

27:08.191 --> 27:11.151
- Go ahead and hate it
because you didn't think of it,

27:11.194 --> 27:13.066
but your stupid carwash,

27:13.109 --> 27:15.503
it's one of the IRS's
first targets

27:15.546 --> 27:17.766
right behind coin laundromats.

27:17.810 --> 27:21.117
I Googled it.
Guess what's not on the list.

27:22.989 --> 27:24.817
Hot tubs.

27:26.601 --> 27:28.690
- They're called spas.

27:30.300 --> 27:33.521
Pay her.
Deduct the artwork.

27:40.702 --> 27:43.270
- Good morning, Mrs. Boland.
- Get him.

27:43.313 --> 27:45.315
- I don't believe that I have
another package for you today.

27:45.359 --> 27:48.492
- Get him.
I have his money.

27:48.536 --> 27:51.887
I just have a few questions.
- Hm?

27:51.931 --> 27:54.324
- What does omakase
have to do with it?

27:54.368 --> 27:56.196
- It means entrusting yourself
to the chef.

27:56.239 --> 27:59.634
Typically off menu,
locally driven, sushi grade--

27:59.678 --> 28:01.375
- I mean how does it help...

28:04.595 --> 28:06.641
With killing a man?

28:06.685 --> 28:08.904
- Your lover enjoys a two-hour
omakase lunch every Friday.

28:08.948 --> 28:10.079
Never misses.

28:10.123 --> 28:12.038
After, he goes out
into the parking lot

28:12.081 --> 28:14.605
and has a chat with the chef.
It's an opportunity.

28:14.649 --> 28:16.477
He then does various business
with people

28:16.520 --> 28:18.653
who would make my work
difficult.

28:18.697 --> 28:20.133
Not an opportunity.

28:20.176 --> 28:22.744
On Tuesdays, he plays tennis
at a very posh country club.

28:22.788 --> 28:25.747
You'll see the charge
for the valet in there.

28:25.791 --> 28:29.272
He does shower after
in an unattended locker room.

28:29.316 --> 28:30.447
It's another opportunity.

28:30.491 --> 28:31.884
You see where
I'm headed with this?

28:31.927 --> 28:33.494
I didn't put in all the details
because then I would

28:33.537 --> 28:36.410
have to charge you for the time
it took to explain them.

28:42.068 --> 28:45.419
- Story of my life.
- What's that?

28:47.813 --> 28:49.597
- Missed opportunities.

28:51.251 --> 28:53.427
- One thing
I couldn't figure out...

28:56.560 --> 29:01.217
Married mother of four,
Junior League, PTA,

29:01.261 --> 29:04.351
winner of the state fair
mini muffin baking competition

29:04.394 --> 29:06.701
three years running.
- You dig deep.

29:08.659 --> 29:10.574
- So how's a lady like you
get involved

29:10.618 --> 29:12.359
with a guy like that?

29:19.540 --> 29:22.282
- I was just bored.

29:27.504 --> 29:31.073
- Tomorrow at noon--
I'll text you the address.

29:31.117 --> 29:34.076
Let me get that for you.
- Thank you.

29:34.120 --> 29:36.383
- I am gonna replace
this thing.

29:42.128 --> 29:44.652
- Oh, my lord!

29:46.349 --> 29:48.830
- I didn't know
what you guys like, so...

29:48.874 --> 29:51.485
- I've never had crepes.

29:51.528 --> 29:52.834
- I did a bit of
everything.

29:52.878 --> 29:54.401
- Ohh!

29:56.751 --> 29:58.709
Mmm.

30:00.189 --> 30:03.323
- So you sleep okay?
Harry's bed's a little tight.

30:03.366 --> 30:06.456
- That comforter
is like sleeping on a cloud.

30:06.500 --> 30:08.545
- Right?
His grandma gave it to him.

30:08.589 --> 30:10.156
- Aw.

30:11.853 --> 30:13.681
You guys are so lucky.

30:19.556 --> 30:21.471
- So I made some sandwiches
for the road,

30:21.515 --> 30:23.909
and we can pack up some treats.

30:23.952 --> 30:25.475
- Oh, you're amazing.

30:25.519 --> 30:27.434
- If there's anything
we can do, don't hesitate.

30:32.656 --> 30:35.181
- How about a car?

30:36.051 --> 30:37.139
- Pardon?

30:37.183 --> 30:40.055
- Mm, Carl's too proud to ask.

30:43.537 --> 30:46.583
- I know it seems
like we're doing okay,

30:46.627 --> 30:48.585
but I promise you,

30:48.629 --> 30:50.544
the struggle
is real everywhere.

30:53.503 --> 30:55.418
- Is it?

30:55.462 --> 30:58.726
- We work triple shifts
and juggle bills,

30:58.769 --> 31:00.597
max out credit cards.

31:00.641 --> 31:04.384
- Your daughter is sleeping
safe in her bed.

31:09.563 --> 31:13.088
- Ooh, is the duchess
coming to breakfast?

31:14.437 --> 31:16.570
- 'Cause this can't be for us.
Is it?

31:16.613 --> 31:19.486
- Honey, that is just
the kind of people they are.

31:19.529 --> 31:22.489
- Well, it's like having
our own restaurant.

31:22.532 --> 31:23.794
Oh.

31:23.838 --> 31:25.927
- Look at that.
I think it's fresh squeezed.

31:28.843 --> 31:30.366
- What is this?

31:30.410 --> 31:32.194
- It's "Naked and Afraid,"
dog.

31:33.369 --> 31:34.849
- You should be studying.

31:34.893 --> 31:37.069
- Look, this girl just ate
part of a dead monkey.

31:39.071 --> 31:40.811
- Why are your books
in the trash?

31:40.855 --> 31:43.945
- I think it's a foot
or a thigh or something,

31:43.989 --> 31:45.077
but now she can't stop pooping.

31:45.120 --> 31:46.513
Hey, hey, whoa, whoa, whoa!

31:46.556 --> 31:47.993
They were just about
to airlift her out.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.342
- You have a test!

31:49.385 --> 31:51.431
- Can you relax?
It got called off.

31:51.474 --> 31:53.085
- By who?

31:53.128 --> 31:54.869
- Me.
- Why?

31:54.913 --> 31:56.392
- Because I'm just not ready.

31:56.436 --> 31:58.960
- You've been studying
for months.

31:59.004 --> 32:01.354
- Look, it's my life, okay?

32:03.095 --> 32:06.098
- Fine.
- Great.

32:07.447 --> 32:10.580
- If you're done, so am I.

32:10.624 --> 32:12.408
- Well--well,
what does that mean?

32:12.452 --> 32:14.628
- I'm not ready either.

32:15.281 --> 32:18.893
- Wha--hey, hey, hey.

32:18.937 --> 32:21.330
What--dah-dah-dah--
Do not.

32:21.374 --> 32:23.506
- "Lord of the Flies"
essay is in here.

32:23.550 --> 32:25.421
- Didn't you back it up?
- Handwritten.

32:25.465 --> 32:27.467
- No.
- Biology book.

32:27.510 --> 32:29.948
No more boring homework
about chloroplasts.

32:29.991 --> 32:31.253
- That is like
half your grade.

32:31.297 --> 32:32.428
- Who needs it?

32:32.472 --> 32:33.777
I'll just work
at the mini mart.

32:33.821 --> 32:35.257
- That is not happening.

32:35.301 --> 32:37.825
- Why not?
Good enough for you.

