37:27.462 --> 37:28.855
- Thank you.

37:30.509 --> 37:32.380
Why'd you change your mind?

37:34.469 --> 37:37.516
- We're alike, you and I.

37:38.821 --> 37:39.953
- I don't know about that.

37:39.996 --> 37:45.088
- I was...just bored too.

37:51.530 --> 37:54.272
- Took you long enough.
- Where is she?

37:56.012 --> 37:57.449
- Well,
couple of options here--

37:57.492 --> 37:59.146
you keep taking it
until you pass

37:59.189 --> 38:02.758
or move to West Virginia
and work the coal mines.

38:02.802 --> 38:03.977
If you bring your own helmet,

38:04.020 --> 38:06.414
I hear they hire you
on the spot.

38:08.938 --> 38:10.810
- They said I tested
on the high end

38:10.853 --> 38:12.768
for a sixth-grader.

38:12.812 --> 38:14.770
- At least it was
on the high end.

38:14.814 --> 38:16.294
- You can go now.

38:17.599 --> 38:19.819
- Right, get up.
- Pass.

38:19.862 --> 38:22.343
- You're coming with me.
- Where?

38:23.953 --> 38:25.738
- Field trip.

38:25.781 --> 38:27.827
Just 'cause I'm British
doesn't mean I play darts...

38:27.870 --> 38:29.089
- Are you sure?

38:29.132 --> 38:31.221
- Or cricket or rowing
or rugby or--

38:31.265 --> 38:33.398
- Oh, oh, of course not
because you don't have any time

38:33.441 --> 38:35.138
'cause you're always
out on a fox hunt.

38:35.182 --> 38:36.836
- I don't go on fox hunts!

38:36.879 --> 38:38.316
- I'm scared of horses.

38:38.359 --> 38:39.621
- Are you really?
- Yeah.

38:39.665 --> 38:43.408
